<div class="page" id="p3">
  <div class="tag">Grammar</div>
  <h1>Defining Relative Clauses 📖</h1>
  <p class="sub">Read the sentences. Pay attention to the words in <span class="hl">purple</span>.</p>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="clb">A — Read and notice</div>
    <div class="ex"><em>Wicked</em> is a musical <span class="hl">that</span> tells the story of two witches.</div>
    <div class="ex">Cynthia Erivo is the actress <span class="hl">who</span> plays Elphaba in <em>Wicked</em>.</div>
    <div class="ex">Hollywood is the place <span class="hl">where</span> most big films are made.</div>
    <div class="ex">2023 was the year <span class="hl">when</span> <em>Barbie</em> and <em>Oppenheimer</em> were released on the same day.</div>
    <div class="ex">Timothée Chalamet is an actor <span class="hl">whose</span> performance made <em>Dune</em> famous.</div>
    <p style="margin-top:14px;font-size:.86rem;color:var(--mu);line-height:1.6">The words in purple connect two ideas. They tell us <em>exactly which</em> person, thing, or place we mean.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="gb">
    <h3>📌 The Rules</h3>
    <table><thead><tr><th>Word</th><th>Use it for</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">who</span></td><td>people</td><td>the director <span class="hl">who</span> made Oppenheimer</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">which</span></td><td>things & animals</td><td>a film <span class="hl">which</span> won many awards</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">that</span></td><td>people or things (informal)</td><td>a story <span class="hl">that</span> everyone loves</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">where</span></td><td>places</td><td>the cinema <span class="hl">where</span> I saw Dune</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">when</span></td><td>times</td><td>the moment <span class="hl">when</span> everything changes</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="hl">whose</span></td><td>possession (people)</td><td>an actress <span class="hl">whose</span> films I love</td></tr>
    </tbody></table>
  </div>
  <div class="gb">
    <h3>⚠️ Important points</h3>
    <p style="font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.8">A <strong>defining</strong> relative clause gives essential information. Without it, we don't know which person or thing is meant.<br><br>✅ "The film <span class="hl">that</span> won the Oscar was <em>Oppenheimer</em>." — we need this clause to know which film.<br><br>❌ Do <strong>not</strong> use commas in defining relative clauses.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="clb">C — Check your understanding</div>
    <div class="disc"><span class="di">💡</span><span>Complete: "The pronoun <em>who</em> is used for ____. The pronoun <em>where</em> is used for ____."</span></div>
    <div class="disc"><span class="di">💡</span><span>Which two pronouns can be used for things?</span></div>
    <div class="disc"><span class="di">💡</span><span>What is different about <em>whose</em>? How is it different from <em>who</em>?</span></div>
  </div>
